                <h3>General Electric (GE)</h3>
                <p>GE cooktops are known for their reliability and advanced features. However, when it comes to repairs, costs can vary based on the specific model and the nature of the issue. Generally, repair costs for GE cooktops can range from <b>$150 to $400</b>. Common problems include faulty burners, malfunctioning control boards, and damaged glass tops. While minor repairs like burner replacements might be on the lower end of the scale, more complex issues such as electronic control board failures can be more expensive. It's advisable to seek service from GE-certified technicians to ensure quality and to potentially benefit from any existing warranties.</p>

                <h3>Whirlpool</h3>
                <p>Whirlpool cooktops are popular for their durability and user-friendly designs. Repair costs for Whirlpool cooktops typically fall between <b>$100 and $350</b>. Common issues include broken knobs, faulty ignition systems, and issues with heating elements. Simple fixes like replacing a knob or a heating coil are generally less expensive, while more intricate repairs involving electronic components can be pricier. Whirlpool offers a network of authorized service providers, and utilizing them can not only ensure proper repairs but also help in maintaining any existing warranties.</p>

