                  <div class="FAQ">
                    <div class="fa">
                      <h3>
                        What should I do if my induction cooktop isn’t detecting the cookware?
                      </h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="fa_plus">︾</div>

                    <div class="fa_minus">︽</div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="questions">
                    <p>If your induction cooktop isn’t detecting the cookware, here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot and resolve the issue:</p>

                    <ol>
                      <li><b>Check Cookware Compatibility: </b>Ensure that the cookware you are using is compatible with induction cooktops. Induction cooktops require magnetic cookware. To test this, try sticking a magnet to the bottom of the pot or pan. If it sticks, the cookware is compatible.</li>
                      <li><b>Flat Bottom Cookware: </b>Make sure that the bottom of your cookware is flat and smooth. Induction cooktops require direct contact with the cookware surface to function properly. Warped or uneven cookware may not be detected.</li>
                      <li><b>Correct Size: </b>Use cookware that matches the size of the induction element. If the cookware is too small for the element, the cooktop might not detect it. Refer to your stove's manual for the recommended size.</li>
                      <li><b>Sensor Issues: </b>Sometimes, the sensors on the induction cooktop can be faulty or dirty. Wipe down the cooktop surface and the bottom of the cookware to ensure there is no residue or debris interfering with the sensors.</li>
                      <li><b>Power Supply: </b>Ensure that your induction cooktop is properly plugged in and receiving power. Sometimes, a loose connection or power issue can affect the cooktop's performance.</li>
                      <li><b>Reset the Cooktop: </b>Try resetting your induction cooktop. This can often resolve minor glitches. Refer to your stove's manual for specific instructions on how to reset the appliance.</li>
                      <li><b>Service Needed: </b>If none of the above steps work, there may be an issue with the cooktop itself. In this case, it might be best to contact a professional appliance repair service. They can diagnose and fix any underlying issues with your induction cooktop.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <p>By following these steps, you can identify and potentially resolve the issue preventing your induction cooktop from detecting the cookware. If you continue to experience problems, don't hesitate to reach out to a professional for help.</p>

